INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("67", "2", "2016-03-18 03:16:46", "2016-03-18 03:16:46", "Learn Programming and Web Design... save a fortune!\n\nIn today\'s competitive market of web designers and Wordpress experts, it can be difficult to choose a company or individual you can trust to design and build your website or blog. If you are a solopreneur or a very small start-up, your website is not only a crucial part of the pulse of your business, but it\'s also one of the most costly expenses if you aren\'t sure of what you are doing. It almost seems like you need an expert just to find a competent solution to your web design woes. Here\'s the crux of the problem...\n\nWhen you are a new business owner, or a business in need of a new website, you are bombarded with literally thousands of options on who to choose, what it should look like, how much you should spend initially, how much it will cost to have it maintained... The list can be daunting and seemingly endless.\n\nWhat if I told you that websites are not as important as you think they are? What if I told you that there are 5 Key Points you need to make and you can secure your online presence...? When a potential customer or client looks you up online, they are probably looking for one of these 5 Key points and everything else is \"bonus\" content. Don\'t believe me? Think of a time you have used the internet to research a company you would like to know more about... What did you want to know the most about them?\n\nJust knowing this will cut down your need for expensive start-up websites maintained remotely at a monthly rate. If you could offer just these 5 Key points and you are willing to learn a new skill... then I am talking to you, my friend. We will cover those exact 5 Key points in a minute but first I want to share with you a quick story...\n\nWhen I was starting my first \"handmade\" business offering jewelry, clothing, and body care items I made at home. I wanted to have my own \"place\" online because I knew it was a pipe dream to have a physical store location. Little did I know, this sad fact turned out to be a huge blessing! When trying to understand the difference between all the products and services web designers had to offer, I became very frustrated with information overload. I was paralyzed with fear because I didn\'t have much to invest in a website, but I knew I needed one that was professional and secure. I almost gave up on the whole idea until a thought occurred to me... What if I could just build it myself? Less than a month later, I had my first website, built in Wordpress and I didn\'t have to pay anyone to do it for me, nor do I have to pay them to maintain it monthly! It\'s incredibly empowering to take control of such an important aspect of my business!\n\nOf course, for some of you out there, you have plenty of money to invest in getting a website built, but you do not have much time to learn the skills. I completely understand this too. Sometimes the better investment is monetary, sometimes it is paid in blood, sweat, and tears. If this is you, keep reading because I am going to tell you the 5 Key Points that any customer is looking for when they look you up online. This is true whether you have a physical store or an online shop. Are you ready?\n\n<strong>1. LOCATION</strong>\nPhysical Address - Website name\n\n<strong>2. CONTACT INFO</strong>\nPhone Number - Email Address\n\n<strong>3. ABOUT YOUR BUSINESS</strong>\nShort story or section explaining what you do, links to social media, credentials\n\n<strong>4. SHOPPING</strong>\nOpportunity to shop online, see a sample of your products, get a list of events you are hosting\n\n<strong>5. DISCOUNTS / COUPONS</strong>\nMany people will check online to see if you offer special discounts or memberships\n\n<strong>BONUS:</strong>\n\n<strong>6. RATING / REVIEWS</strong>\nIf you have great customers who love you, add their testimonials and photos so your prospective customer can see how great you are at what you do\n\nHow do you learn to build a website? There are almost as many ways to learn as there are ways to buy a website... Here <a href=\"http://megmillerhilo.com/step-by-step-training/\">http://www.megmillerhilo.com/step-by-step-training</a> is my quick tutorial on how to get a basic website or blog, with all the information listed above, designed and created for under $25. Right now, this training is FREE for anyone who is interested in learning to build from scratchor would like to learn to maintain their existing site. If you decide to have a website built for you, now you know the bare minimum of what your customers will likely be searching for in the first place.\n\nTo sign up for more information on running a successful business and mastering your marketing, click here to get the<a href=\"http://www.megmillerhilo.com/answers\" target=\"_blank\">ANSWERS</a>start your journey with a Free Online Workshop. Once you attend, you will have the opportunity to connect with hundreds of members worldwide, and gain access to all the training you will need to start a businessor to start using these trends in your marketing today. Looking forward to seeing you there!\n\n<span class=\"sign\">Meg Miller</span>", "To Build it or to Buy it, That is the Question...", "", "publish", "open", "open", "", "to-build-it-or-to-buy-it-that-is-the-question", "", "", "2016-03-18 03:16:46", "2016-03-18 03:16:46", "", "0", "http://megmillerhilo.com/?p=67", "0", "post", "", "0");
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("500", "2", "2016-04-04 12:18:23", "2016-04-04 12:18:23", "In today\'s fast-paced, high-touch world, we are constantly updating our social network status, checking-in to places, posting pictures of our food and our families (not necessarily in that order)... We are connected to the global community 24/7/365 and no matter what you think, everything you do matters. If you are running any kind of business, whether it\'s a multi-national corporation or a solo-preneur enterprise you run from the kitchen table, everything you do is marketing your brand. Brand recognition is a powerful driving force behind the success of any business so it is vitally important that you are being recognized for the right reasons.\n\nHigh-profile members of our society have learned this lesson the hard way time after time and we sit back and wonder how they keep getting themselves involved in such bad PR. Have you ever considered that your own life works in much the same way?\n\nTake for instance that noisy neighbor situation. (Hypothetically, of course!) You absolutely have the right, on your own personal accounts, to complain and broadcast your problem to any potential sympathetic friend out there. They will probably give you some phrases of encouragement and support and maybe a few will offer to \"solve\" your problem for you. It can be nice to have a negative experience and make light of it by sharing the load with your friends. However, if your business and your personal character are connected, which they undoubtedly are unless you are a faceless CEO, then you are getting yourself involved in bad PR.\n\nThe world keeps getting smaller, and everything you do is being watched by someone. People judge without knowing the facts and this can permanently damage your reputation as a business owner. Complaining may feel good at the time, and it may give you ideas on how to solve the problem, but perhaps you could just skip to the end and ask for advice on how to handle the problem...?\n\nEverything you do is marketing so why not use it to put a positive spin on everything? Even if you have a terrible tragedy and you want to share it, you can phrase it in a way that invites solutions, motivation, true support and whatever else you may need to improve the situation.\n\nOn the flip side, if you are sharing as many positive experiences as possible, then people will see you as a reputable source for their needs. People always respond better to proactive, happy people who are putting in effort. Say you landed a big client and you will be doubling your income this year... Just like there is a way to \"complain\" creatively without being negative, there is a way to celebrate creatively without bragging or inflating yourself beyond what people see you as being. You could share that you landed a great deal which will significantly improve your income... vs. sharing that you landed a rich client and doubled your income for the year already... The way you present yourself and the way people will receive you are ultimately the same thing. Keep that in mind when you are publicizing any aspect of your personal life.\n\nOne more way that you can improve your marketing relationship with your personal life is to show genuine gratitude when you get something you want. When you hit milestones or collaborate with a team, when you have a record profit this month or when you sell record units; share it with gratitude for yourself, for your efforts and for those who helped you along the way. I am not suggesting that every good thing needs to be accompanied by a full-on acceptance speech like you are at the AMAs, but when it comes to the major events, showing gratitude will attract people to you personally and professionally.\n\nIf you have an Instagram account, keep in mind that your personal photos, in a public forum aren\'t very personal anymore. If you are out having a great time and you take some photos, that\'s fantastic!! I agree that we, as owners, shouldn\'t become total prudes. However, if you have had a few drinks, maybe you should not be posting to the internet until your business (and more sober) side can take a look and see how you come across to any clients or prospects that may see them. If you go to the beach, make sure you are comfortable with the idea that your 2:00 Monday afternoon appointment may happen to see you sprawled out with a pile of empty bottles next to your mostly naked beach body. Images rarely tell the whole story and people will think what they want to think and fill in any blanks with amazing imaginative abilities. It may be a fact that only one empty bottle is actually yours, but the picture tells a different story. Just be careful that it\'s the story you are trying to share! If you wouldn\'t show it to your Grandmother, then you should think twice about sharing it in a public venue. *wink*\n\nWhile we would all like to have a way to seperate our personal from our business personas, this is only possible to a degree. As the world changes and communication methods become faster and more accessible to people, we would all do well to keep in mind that while they are not always paying attention, someone is likely to always be watching. Following a few simple rules you set for yourself will improve your brand image and your personal persona. Keep it on the lighter side and people will definitely notice.\n\nPlease subscribe by clicking the \"Subscribe for Updates\" button at the top of this page, or the \"Get Updates\" button at the bottom of this page. I send out messages only when new content is added or has a major update. Thanks for sharing!\n\nTo sign up for more information on running a successful business and mastering your marketing, click here: www.megmillerhilo.com/answers and sign up for a Free Live training webcast. Once you attend, you will have the opportunity to connect with hundreds of members world-wide, and gain access to all the training you will need to start a business, or to start using these trends in your marketing today. Hope to see you there!\n\n- Meg", "Everything You Do is Marketing...", "", "publish", "open", "open", "", "everything-you-do-is-marketing", "", "", "2016-04-04 12:18:23", "2016-04-04 12:18:23", "", "0", "http://megmillerhilo.com/?p=500", "0", "post", "", "0");
