INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("531", "2", "2016-04-21 22:43:12", "2016-04-21 22:43:12", "So you have decided you want to be successful? What makes some people super successful and others fall behind? What is the difference between you and them? There are limitless articles and blogs about what you can do to be more efficient as a business owner, but what about just being a better version of yourself in general? What are you doing to improve yourself in ways that will not only benefit your business, but also benefit every aspect of your daily life?\n\nGet your notebook handy and be ready to jot down some tips that top earners are using to be super successful not only in business but in their personal lives. Listen as Paki, Gem, Jerry along with Joe and I (Meg), discuss some of the most important changes we have made and what resources we used to make them. As you watch the entire video below, and as you follow along and take notes, think about what you are doing to improve yourself daily. After you finish the video, jot down your daily actions under your notes and see what you can add to your routine to make your life more enjoyable. Having a clear intention in mind when you begin a task will help you focus and allow you to get more from what you are learning. Enjoy and we all look forward to working with you soon!\n\n<iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/kPlLxKXtQlY\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe>\n\nIf you are interested in joining our team, sign up to attend your Introduction webinar to learn more about the Simple System we have all used to find success in earning an income online. Click here to get <a href=\"http://megmillerhilo.com/answers/\" target=\"_blank\">Answers</a>.", "Why Personal Development is Your One Key to Happiness", "", "publish", "open", "open", "", "april-19-2016-importance-of-personal-development", "", "", "2016-04-21 22:43:12", "2016-04-21 22:43:12", "", "0", "http://megmillerhilo.com/?p=531", "0", "post", "", "0");
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("548", "3", "2016-08-24 05:26:00", "2016-08-24 05:26:00", "When you fly out of Hilo to pretty much anywhere, your route takes you directly over the beautiful island of Maui. The views from the plane are at worst stunning and at best intoxicating as the two gorgeous mountains perfectly frame the thin patch of red and green earth rolling between two gleaming shores. Every time we would fly over, Meg and I would look down longingly from thousands of feet above and say, \"We will visit... soon.\" It was that word, \"soon\", that kept throwing us off from actually making a plan to go and visit what we knew would be a paradise rivaling the one we currently live on.\n\n\"Soon\" has become to me one of the \"danger words\" that is a clear sign of hesitation, worry, and lack beliefs. In the last few months, I have come to understand that there is no such thing as \"soon\". Soon is a non-specific deferral that puts the target permanently out of reach relative to \"now.\" Think about it; has anything actually ever happened to you \"soon\"? I highly doubt it and if so, I\'m sure that must be an interesting story (possibly involving a T.A.R.D.I.S.). The point here is that using the word \"soon\" is basically like an automatic procrastinator that puts the thing you want just out of reach.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_14\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"676\"]<img class=\"wp-image-14 size-large\" src=\"http://makeyourliving.info/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/IMG_1146-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"The beautiful island of Maui from the plane while flying over.\" width=\"676\" height=\"507\" /> Maui when viewed from the \"soon\" mindset. Notice that is is sparkly and beautiful, but very very far away...[/caption]\n\nSo this time, when we heard that some of our business team were meeting over on Maui, we decided to (finally!) unhitch from our \"soon\" mentality and pull that experience into the \"now\". We asked ourselves, \"How can we do this?\" rather than telling ourselves we couldn\'t. The effect was immediate and immense. A week later, we were getting ready to board our flight. \"Now\" is where life happens. When you have a great experience, you are experiencing it now, not \"soon\", not \"later\", but now!\n\n&nbsp;\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_6\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"676\"]<img class=\"wp-image-6 size-large\" src=\"http://makeyourliving.info/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/P8190045-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"Meg, Joe, and Kathleen explore breathtaking Twin Falls\" width=\"676\" height=\"507\" /> Meg and I with our AMAZING friend and business teammate Kathleen at the gorgeous Twin Falls park. Meeting up with Kathleen was the real highlight of our trip![/caption]\n\nWe had the trip of a lifetime. We spent 2 jam packed days taking in as much of Maui as we could (and it actually felt more like 5 days!). Traveling, meeting up with friends, having adventures; these are all by-products of the \"now\" mindset. So I wanted to know how best to root myself in that state. For Meg, it wasn\'t so hard. She\'s been living predominately in the now for as long as I\'ve known her. For me though, it was more of a struggle. I had always been one to put things off, to save it for later, to work hard now, and have fun when I retire.\n\nSoon is for Suckers. I have been awakening to this idea since we started our online business. Just taking that first big step broke the seal on the metaphorical pressure cooker of my stagnant mindset. It was like all of these fears of lack, worries about money and stuff, over-analysis of my future course, etc. started to escape, which left room for new and better things to grow in my head. Things like success, wonder, abundance, and freedom. Over the last 9 months I have seen my life transform in a way I couldn\'t have imagined back then. And it all started with that single step!\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_97\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"1024\"]<img class=\"wp-image-97 size-large\" src=\"http://makeyourliving.info/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/P8190139-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"Since taking that first step to be bold and live more fully, my feet have seen some awesome places!\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\" /> Since taking that first step to be bold and live more fully, my feet have seen some awesome places![/caption]\n\nWhatever it is you want to do, see or achieve in life, it all has to start by nixing \"soon\" from your vocabulary. Don\'t let yourself get drawn into the carrot-on-a-stick chase that \"soon\" will bring you. If there\'s anything I\'ve learned about living more freely in tune with my true passions, it\'s to figure out what the first step is, and take it NOW! No more waiting for a better time, no more list of reasons why you can\'t, just pick something and do it already (I\'m mostly yelling at myself here, so don\'t be alarmed)! You really can be, do, and have all the good things you want in life so the question is, do you want it now, or \"soon\"?\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_101\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"768\"]<img class=\"wp-image-101 size-large\" src=\"http://makeyourliving.info/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/meg-joe-arch-kiss-upright-768x1024.jpg\" alt=\"OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA\" width=\"768\" height=\"1024\" /> OLYMPUS DIGITAL CAMERA[/caption]", "Soon is for Suckers! (Maui Nowi)", "", "publish", "open", "open", "", "maui-nowi", "", "", "2016-08-24 05:26:00", "2016-08-24 05:26:00", "", "0", "http://makeyourliving.info/?p=5", "0", "post", "", "0");
